                            <comment id="17027918" author="reuvenlax" created="Sat, 1 Feb 2020 01:03:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is more general: if an input bundle contains both element and timers, the effect of processing the elements does not affect the timers in the bundle. So assume an input bundle contains an element E and a timer T set for 12pm. While processing E, the user resets the timer T to be at 1pm. Correct behavior would be to skip the timer in this bundle, as it&apos;s no longer eligible to fire, however today it will still fire.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
